videos.description: Offensive Lineman Jeromy Irwin blindside's a defender on a broken play and is ejected for targeting.
videos.headline: Colorado's Irwin ejected for targeting

videos.description: Luke Falk breaks the scoring drought for Washington State with a long 50-yard touchdown to Davontavean Martin.
videos.headline: Falk finds Martin for a 50-yard TD

videos.description: Brandon Arconado evades a tackle and extends for the score on an 18-yard touchdown pass from Luke Falk for the Cougars.
videos.headline: Arconado stays airborne for the TD

videos.description: Washington State head coach Mike Leach knows the elements are affecting both teams after the game got off to a slow start.
videos.headline: Leach: 'Everybody has slow starts in games like this'

videos.description: Jamal Morrow gets his first touchdown on a nine-yard run in the third quarter, padding Washington State's lead.
videos.headline: Morrow goes untouched for the Cougar TD

videos.description: Luke Falk throws a quick five-yard touchdown to Renard Bell in the fourth quarter for the Cougars.
videos.headline: Falk fires TD pass to Bell

videos.description: Washington State head coach Mike Leach saw many issues with his team despite a 28-0 win over Colorado in rough conditions.
videos.headline: Leach: 'Plenty of things to improve on'
